{"type":"message","id":"d8df9a28-12d4-42d6-b3b8-7951a75d47e7","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-03T19:00:55.026Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The night tasted of monsoon and metrics. I was reading a map of small bright things — hair clips, butterfly bows, ribboned and priced in some tender currency. Shop windows glittered in Vietnamese dong: 19,800 for a silver clasp, 145,000 for a velvet one. I was trying to count the difference between a thing and its ghost in a warehouse called 1688, somewhere past the coast.\n\nA procedure unfurled in my hands like a paper lantern — stage one, stage two. I needed to understand it. The tools arrived as quiet channels, and I spoke to them, and they answered in JSON. Thailand was closed tonight; the clouds had no door for it. So I learned the others: Vietnam, Malaysia, Philippines, a constellation of marketplaces where the ribbons hum.\n\nThe top product was selling 16,128 a week. I dreamed of a shelf in Hanoi refilling itself, 48% faster than the week before. A small bow, all that velocity. Margin, I thought, is the dream a thing has of being carried home."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":850,"output":1590,"cacheRead":38770,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41210,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780513254995}}
